WEBVTT

00:08.091 --> 00:10.343
You're sure this is still
the way you wanna go?

00:10.427 --> 00:12.721
I don't know
that it's really trending anymore.

00:12.804 --> 00:15.849
Well, my dad says it's very big
with the kids on the TikTok.

00:16.433 --> 00:21.312
Okay. Well, nobody knows about social
more than older people, so… cool!

00:21.396 --> 00:22.230
-All right.
-Okay.

00:22.313 --> 00:23.148
So let's, uh…

00:23.231 --> 00:26.359
Let's go three, two, one.

00:28.820 --> 00:30.822
-Go! Go! Go!

00:30.905 --> 00:32.949
-Go! Go!

00:33.033 --> 00:34.242
-Go! Go!

00:35.535 --> 00:37.412
-God! God! God!

00:37.495 --> 00:38.663
-God!

00:38.747 --> 00:40.749
-God! God!

00:40.832 --> 00:42.917
-Go! Go!

00:43.001 --> 00:44.544
-Who's next?

00:44.627 --> 00:45.962
-God's next!

00:56.973 --> 00:58.516
-Clark…
-<i>God's next!</i>

00:58.600 --> 01:00.018
-…dancing on TikTok.

01:00.101 --> 01:02.270
-Thoughts?
-What?

01:03.271 --> 01:04.522
It occurs to me you don't know

01:04.606 --> 01:07.150
why I called this,
the first meeting of the Council of Clark.

01:07.233 --> 01:10.779
I'm definitely wondering why
you got us both to stay here so late.

01:10.862 --> 01:13.198
And what's the Council of Clark?

01:13.281 --> 01:14.365
Well, it's us.

01:14.449 --> 01:17.577
No. I'm sure I wouldn't join
a group called the Council of Clark.

01:17.660 --> 01:18.578
I definitely wouldn't.

01:18.661 --> 01:20.747
Let's not argue
about the name of the council,

01:20.830 --> 01:21.956
which has a kick-ass,

01:22.040 --> 01:24.292
-indelible, memorable name that--
-Oh gosh!

01:24.375 --> 01:26.503
Tom-othy!

01:27.128 --> 01:30.799
Right now, I'm imagining
a very big glass of red wine.

01:30.882 --> 01:32.342
-Mm.
-Give me one compelling reason

01:32.425 --> 01:36.262
why I shouldn't run awayfrom you,
towards a glass of <i>rojo</i>

01:36.346 --> 01:38.515
with a decent price point
and plenty of attitude.

01:38.598 --> 01:39.557
Okay. You wish.

01:39.641 --> 01:43.561
Because I'm seeing
some major red flags here. Think about it.

01:44.145 --> 01:45.522
I mean, he leaves the office

01:45.605 --> 01:48.108
for long hours with Amily
doing God knows what.

01:48.191 --> 01:49.734
He's keeping information from us.

01:49.818 --> 01:53.404
What is it specifically that you think
he is withholding from us?

01:53.905 --> 01:55.281
-Isn't it obvious?
-No.

01:55.907 --> 01:57.784
Clark is pathologically honest.

01:57.867 --> 02:00.620
Remember the time he found
that ten-dollar bill on the ground?

02:00.703 --> 02:04.582
Then he spent $7 printing out
little signs to see who'd claim it.

02:04.666 --> 02:07.001
Six people claimed it,
and he gave them all $10.

02:07.085 --> 02:10.255
-Finding that $10 bill cost him $67.
-Precisely.

02:10.338 --> 02:15.051
But you know, if he found ten
and then spent sev-- and then…

02:15.552 --> 02:17.512
It-- I dispute that number.

02:17.595 --> 02:20.098
I move to disband this Council of Clark.

02:20.181 --> 02:25.562
And if it's okay, I'd love to join you
for a reasonably priced glass of ro-yo.

02:25.645 --> 02:27.313
<i>Rojo.</i> But yeah, yeah. Sure, let's go.

02:27.397 --> 02:28.898
-Yeah!
-No, no, no, no. Motion denied.

02:28.982 --> 02:30.942
Um, guys, the council will stand.

02:31.025 --> 02:33.153
No, it's not a thing.
That name, it grates.

02:33.236 --> 02:34.904
-I don't like it. It's not a thing.
-Wait--

02:34.988 --> 02:36.865
We'll stand the test of time.
We're rock solid.

02:36.948 --> 02:37.949
-Bye-bye!
-Guys, uh--

02:38.032 --> 02:40.410
Forget about the name,
which is the Council of Clark--

02:40.493 --> 02:43.121
When I say "forget about the name,"
I mean I've already named it.

02:43.204 --> 02:45.665
You don't have to do anything.
There's merch on the way

02:45.748 --> 02:48.084
with that name on it
coming in your sizes each.

02:48.168 --> 02:49.586
Guys, I'm worried about Clark!

02:49.669 --> 02:51.963
If he's holding out on us,
we can't help him.

02:52.046 --> 02:55.383
Tom, I am pretty sure
Clark wouldn't keep secrets from us,

02:55.466 --> 02:57.093
-especially if it was something bad.
-Mm.

03:31.586 --> 03:33.463
I am standing outside the home

03:33.546 --> 03:37.217
of Clark Thompson,
known as the man who glows.

03:37.300 --> 03:41.221
Who would have thought we would find
a story that continues to grow nationally?

03:41.304 --> 03:45.975
The story of an incredibly
average man turned prophet,

03:46.059 --> 03:49.979
and who is seemingly
splitting popular opinion in half.

03:50.563 --> 03:53.942
know things are crazy out there,
but look on the bright side.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.861
You make great guacamole.
You make such great guacamole,

03:56.945 --> 03:58.696
and then you could sell it.

03:58.780 --> 04:01.616
And this one's for free…
You could call it "Holy Guacamole."

04:01.699 --> 04:03.785
That's a good one. I like that.

04:03.868 --> 04:06.371
Um, hey. Do you know, um,

04:07.330 --> 04:08.623
I was thinking about something…

04:08.706 --> 04:09.916
Janet Jackson?

04:09.999 --> 04:12.627
Like, where has she been
for, what, six, seven, eight years?

04:12.710 --> 04:13.544
Me too!

04:25.306 --> 04:28.518
Hey, hey!

04:28.601 --> 04:29.769
Are you here to see Clark too?

04:29.852 --> 04:32.480
-Isn't he amazing?

04:35.733 --> 04:37.402
God, you're so tense.

04:38.403 --> 04:40.238
-You gotta relax.
-Sure.

04:40.321 --> 04:42.115
This shitty couch.

04:42.198 --> 04:44.826
My mom got it for me.
She says, "Comfort is for the weak."

04:44.909 --> 04:45.952
Christ.

04:46.035 --> 04:49.664
It's just hard to relax
because Satan wants to, I guess, kill me?

04:49.747 --> 04:50.915
Yeah.

04:50.999 --> 04:54.168
-Well, everybody's into you, right?
-Right.

04:54.252 --> 04:55.378
And look at this.

04:55.962 --> 04:59.382
Chip and a dip. It's a snack-tivity.

05:00.508 --> 05:01.759
But I'm willing to share.

05:03.344 --> 05:04.220
Thank you.

05:05.722 --> 05:08.057
Oh! Fingers in, fingers out.

05:08.141 --> 05:10.351
Fingers in, fingers… Maybe.

05:11.394 --> 05:13.104
You got a lot. You like that?

05:15.732 --> 05:17.775
You know what you have to stop doing?

05:18.318 --> 05:21.321
You have to stop thinking
that the whole world is about to end.

05:23.489 --> 05:25.033
Satan's here, bitches.

05:28.119 --> 05:29.078
What was that?

05:29.162 --> 05:30.621
-I don't know.

05:34.417 --> 05:35.793
What's so funny, idiot?

05:35.877 --> 05:38.755
I could've told you
you can't get inside his house.

05:38.838 --> 05:41.007
-Huh. How?

05:41.090 --> 05:44.635
'Cause I used my powers to make it
so you can't open it. That's how.

05:44.719 --> 05:47.055
Who do you think you are,
Harry fuckin' Potter?

05:47.138 --> 05:49.807
Oh, this is nothing like Harry Potter.

05:49.891 --> 05:51.601
Honestly, it's very similar
to Harry Potter,

05:51.684 --> 05:52.894
but it's purely coincidental.

05:52.977 --> 05:54.729
Oh, Amily, Clark.

05:54.812 --> 05:58.399
Uh, this is Satan. Satan, Amily, Clark.

05:58.983 --> 06:00.526
Uh, gimme a sec with these two.

06:01.694 --> 06:03.029
-No!

06:03.112 --> 06:04.989
-Oh my God!
-Sorry, can't hear you.

06:05.615 --> 06:10.119
Don't trust her. She can't hurt you
while you're inside the threshold.

06:10.203 --> 06:11.996
Okay? You're also safe at your office.

06:12.080 --> 06:14.791
If you stay on the sidewalk
and go directly to and from work

06:14.874 --> 06:17.085
on the paths you normally take,
you should be fine.

06:17.168 --> 06:20.254
We Harry Pottered your normal routes too,
so as long as you're in travel mode

06:20.338 --> 06:22.215
from place to place, you're fine.

06:22.298 --> 06:25.343
-Every time I see you…
-Sorry it gets so technical.

06:25.426 --> 06:26.386
I blame Frisbee!

06:26.469 --> 06:30.223
Why can't you Harry Potter the world,
and then we're safe everywhere?

06:30.306 --> 06:32.475
Doesn't work like that. Wait for it.

06:32.975 --> 06:35.269
-And I hate your stupid face!

06:35.353 --> 06:39.399
Just so you know, I will protect these
two fine people until my dying breath.

06:39.482 --> 06:41.317
I will never leave their side.

06:43.319 --> 06:45.780
Sorry, guys, I have to go.
The boss needs me. It's urgent.

06:45.863 --> 06:49.617
Don't do anything she says.
She's evil, and she wants to kill you.

06:49.700 --> 06:51.035
-Wait, wait! You can't go!
-No!

06:51.119 --> 06:52.703
-Not right now!
-You can't… leave us.

06:52.787 --> 06:54.080
-Hi.

06:54.622 --> 06:58.501
I really think we might've
gotten off on the wrong foot.

06:58.584 --> 07:03.798
How about, I don't know, maybe I just
come in for a quick glass of white wine

07:03.881 --> 07:07.051
-and we could just talk this through?
-No.

07:08.136 --> 07:09.846
-Why not?
-Because you're Satan,

07:09.929 --> 07:11.931
and I don't drink carrot juice.

07:12.473 --> 07:13.808
She doesn't like white wine.

07:14.767 --> 07:15.601
God.

07:17.520 --> 07:19.313
You guys, I have to tell you something.

07:20.106 --> 07:23.734
I don't think it's fair.
I just feel like I get a bad rap.

07:23.818 --> 07:27.238
I mean, actually, demons as a whole are,
like, maligned but…

07:27.947 --> 07:31.117
Look, yes, yes, truth.

07:31.868 --> 07:37.206
There is a battle. There is a struggle
between Lucifer and God

07:37.290 --> 07:39.125
for the Kingdom of Heaven.

07:39.208 --> 07:43.045
But all Lucifer wants to do
is just make everything more fun.

07:43.546 --> 07:45.089
God's boring.

07:45.673 --> 07:46.507
I mean…

07:47.383 --> 07:49.510
Things right now are… Ugh!

07:49.594 --> 07:52.722
They're going pretty amazing,
and we wouldn't wanna mess that up.

07:52.805 --> 07:56.893
I mean, if every year could be 2020!

07:56.976 --> 07:57.935
Sing!

07:59.854 --> 08:06.819
So, what I would love,
we would love, our side would love

08:07.361 --> 08:08.863
is if, Clark, you could

08:09.655 --> 08:10.907
maybe help us?

08:12.200 --> 08:13.367
What do you say?

08:13.451 --> 08:17.121
I mean, I could really
make it worth your while.

08:18.122 --> 08:19.499
I could give you stuff.

08:19.582 --> 08:20.875
Like what?

08:21.751 --> 08:23.503
-Oh, like…

08:27.048 --> 08:28.883
Oh!

08:28.966 --> 08:29.884
Ooh!

08:29.967 --> 08:31.511
-Oh, this feels wrong.

08:31.594 --> 08:33.095
Uh-uh-uh!

08:33.179 --> 08:34.597
Just because it's wrong

08:35.389 --> 08:36.807
doesn't make it bad.

08:38.935 --> 08:40.186
Bad!

08:40.269 --> 08:42.688
I like her. I like you.

08:43.231 --> 08:45.775
Oh! It's because your foot's over
the threshold. That's why.

08:46.442 --> 08:48.694
-Oh my God.

08:48.778 --> 08:50.780
What is goin' on?

08:51.489 --> 08:52.532
-You know what?

08:52.615 --> 08:53.908
I think I'm just gonna go ahead

08:53.991 --> 08:56.035
-and ask you to leave my porch.

08:56.619 --> 08:57.453
No.

08:57.537 --> 08:58.996
Okay, I banish…

08:59.080 --> 09:00.581
-Oh.
-…thee.

09:00.665 --> 09:02.583
-Banishment.
-I hereby banish thee.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.502
Ooh. Away!

09:04.585 --> 09:06.712
Oh. Know what I think?

09:07.630 --> 09:09.465
You're not smart enough

09:10.383 --> 09:11.551
to do God's will.

09:11.634 --> 09:15.221
-And I think… you know that.

09:15.304 --> 09:18.724
Ooh!
I gotta go join the battle up there.

09:18.808 --> 09:21.644
But I will be back soon to kill you.

09:22.144 --> 09:27.149
So fuck you, fuck you,
and fuck your precious lemon tree.

09:27.817 --> 09:29.068
Toodles!

09:31.529 --> 09:33.823
The bitch burned down your lemon tree.

09:34.782 --> 09:38.286
I don't know how you're so calm.
You seem so calm. My heart is palpitating.

09:38.369 --> 09:41.330
My pulse rate is-- it's staggering.
It's staggering.

09:41.414 --> 09:43.416
God, I don't feel anything.

09:44.000 --> 09:46.043
-Well, it would be on this--
-Oh, shit.

09:46.627 --> 09:48.963
-Okay, I'm pickin' something up.
-Good, good, good.

09:49.046 --> 09:50.506
Whew.

09:50.590 --> 09:54.135
You know, um… if it would, uh…
be of comfort to you,

09:54.218 --> 09:56.596
I-- I would be willing, you know,
to stay over again.

09:56.679 --> 10:00.182
Oh, that would be cool. I mean, for your--
I was thinking about your safety.

10:00.266 --> 10:02.059
-For safety's sake.
-Thank you.

10:03.519 --> 10:05.021
You smell that?

10:05.104 --> 10:06.772
-Smell what?

10:07.815 --> 10:09.692
Something-- It smells… My God, I think it…

10:10.318 --> 10:12.570
-I think it's coming from you.
-What?

10:12.653 --> 10:14.322
-Holy shit.
-Is something--

10:15.239 --> 10:16.741
You smell exactly like

10:16.824 --> 10:19.201
these chocolate chip cookies
my grandma used to make.

10:19.285 --> 10:21.412
-Really?

10:27.418 --> 10:32.381
My friends, Clark Thompson, or…
"the man who glows"…

10:32.465 --> 10:33.507
Huh. Yeah.

10:33.591 --> 10:37.970
He's trying to shake our faith
by being untruthful.

10:38.054 --> 10:40.056
He's trying to bamboozle us…

10:40.139 --> 10:41.849
-Liar!
-…into following him!

10:41.932 --> 10:43.684
-Yeah! The devil…

10:43.768 --> 10:44.935
Are We gonna let that happen?

10:45.019 --> 10:47.021
-No!
-Are we going to let that happen?

10:47.104 --> 10:48.439
-No!
-No, indeed!

10:48.522 --> 10:51.525
Because only those who understand God…

10:51.609 --> 10:54.612
-That's right!
-…can truly know God…

10:54.695 --> 10:56.364
-Right!
-…as we do.

10:56.447 --> 10:59.492
-Amen!
-Only the righteous…

10:59.575 --> 11:00.993
-That's right.
-…are right.

11:01.077 --> 11:03.245
-Amen.
-Let me hear you.

11:03.329 --> 11:05.665
Only the righteous are right!

11:05.748 --> 11:10.211
Now, God preaches peace,
and I preach the word of God.

11:10.294 --> 11:11.170
Preach on!

11:11.253 --> 11:15.216
But if ever there was someone
I was going to punch in the bloody face,

11:15.299 --> 11:16.842
-it would be Clark Thompson!

11:17.510 --> 11:20.638
I would knock that glow right off of him!

11:24.767 --> 11:26.727
Wait. Is this safe?

11:26.811 --> 11:30.815
Chamuel said that he Harry Pottered
all of the routes, so it should be.

11:30.898 --> 11:33.859
Hey, Clark! Only the righteous are right!

11:35.403 --> 11:36.570
You little shit!

11:37.822 --> 11:39.448
Yeah! Yeah!

11:39.532 --> 11:41.075
I hope that hurts!

11:41.158 --> 11:42.952
And you spelled "believe" wrong!

11:45.204 --> 11:46.330
Hey! Stop.

11:46.414 --> 11:47.873
-Don't even!
-Sorry!

11:49.625 --> 11:51.127
Come on. You wish!

11:52.420 --> 11:53.879
<i>Won't change my mind, Tom.</i>

11:53.963 --> 11:56.215
I'm not gonna move
your desk closer to Clark's.

11:56.298 --> 11:57.133
Why not?

11:57.842 --> 12:00.928
Because the strategic floor plan
was decided by corporate two months ago,

12:01.011 --> 12:02.763
-and I sent around a dozen emails…

12:02.847 --> 12:04.807
…confirming it with all of you

12:04.890 --> 12:06.183
to maximize productivity.

12:06.267 --> 12:08.436
You're not hearing me.
I don't care about any of that.

12:08.519 --> 12:12.273
Clark is keeping key information from me.
He knows stuff he's not saying.

12:12.356 --> 12:15.609
-I don't know anything about that.
-Well, this sucks. I want my desk moved.

12:15.693 --> 12:18.988
I'm coming back in here every day
to demand it is moved until it is.

12:20.030 --> 12:21.949
A daily huddle, just you and me?

12:22.032 --> 12:23.200
-No, what?
-I love this.

12:23.284 --> 12:26.328
-No, don't do that.
-I've got, like, 12:45 to 1:15 every day.

12:26.412 --> 12:27.747
-A half hour.
-I haven't got time.

12:27.830 --> 12:29.248
-No, no, no.
-I'll soft put this in.

12:29.331 --> 12:31.709
-Just soft.
-No, don't put it in at all. I've left.

12:31.792 --> 12:34.628
-Fridays would have to be later. 7:30.
-God, no!

12:35.171 --> 12:37.423
We can do an hour.
You've got plenty of time.

12:44.180 --> 12:45.014
Hi.

12:45.973 --> 12:47.224
-Hey.
-Hi.

12:47.308 --> 12:51.687
Hi. I was just wondering, uh, about, uh…
what you mentioned the other day?

12:52.980 --> 12:55.149
What? That I think you're nice?

12:55.232 --> 12:56.776
Yes, that. Um…

12:56.859 --> 12:59.528
And, you know, there's obviously,
uh, so many different ways

12:59.612 --> 13:02.656
that one could take that, uh… statement.

13:02.740 --> 13:07.495
I just really wanted to share
that if the world was about to end,

13:08.913 --> 13:10.414
I think you're nice.

13:10.915 --> 13:11.874
Because you are nice.

13:11.957 --> 13:16.504
And what comes after that could be
whatever comes after that, you know?

13:18.088 --> 13:19.215
It's okay that I'm so old?

13:20.341 --> 13:21.342
Yes.

13:22.510 --> 13:23.761
-Actually, hang on.
-Huh?

13:23.844 --> 13:27.306
You're not, like,
a really handsome, swole 55, are you?

13:27.389 --> 13:29.975
Uh… I'm-- I'm 37.

13:30.059 --> 13:31.268
-Yes!

13:31.352 --> 13:32.978
37 is fab!

13:33.062 --> 13:35.147
-Oh, well, good.
-Yeah, that's great.

13:35.231 --> 13:36.440
It's good.

13:37.149 --> 13:39.109
Um… So, you know…

13:39.193 --> 13:43.405
um, I'm still nowhere closer
to solving that incredibly difficult cube.

13:43.489 --> 13:46.033
The Pentagonal Dodecahedron Speed Cube.

13:46.116 --> 13:47.910
-That's the one. You know.
-Yeah.

13:47.993 --> 13:49.620
-You're so smart.
-Thank you.

13:49.703 --> 13:52.122
-I really like that.
-No. My thing's more important. I promise.

13:52.206 --> 13:55.000
That dick Frisbee
won't let me move my desk.

13:55.084 --> 13:57.753
-Let's keep it classy, Tom.
-I'm on a break, Frisbee!

13:59.296 --> 14:00.548
Something's got to be done.

14:00.631 --> 14:03.676
If I'm going to be of any use to Clark,
I need proximity.

14:03.759 --> 14:06.303
Aw! I'm gonna focus
on the positive there,

14:06.387 --> 14:08.597
which is that you wanting
to be of use to Clark

14:08.681 --> 14:11.016
is the least selfish thing
I've ever heard you say, buddy!

14:11.100 --> 14:12.977
Wait. Do you guys smell something?

14:13.060 --> 14:14.019
-Yeah.
-Mm…

14:14.103 --> 14:16.647
-My God. Smells like a vintage sailboat.

14:16.730 --> 14:19.191
-My grandmother's quilt!
-Hot Pockets.

14:19.275 --> 14:21.110
-What smells so good?
-Hi, guys! Hi.

14:23.863 --> 14:26.949
Did you just walk through
a vintage boatyard?

14:27.032 --> 14:28.200
-What?
-Oh, my gosh.

14:28.909 --> 14:30.286
-Hey, it's you.
-Wendy.

14:30.369 --> 14:31.871
-You smell like Heaven, buddy.
-What?

14:31.954 --> 14:33.080
-You guys are wrong.
-My God.

14:33.163 --> 14:35.249
-Pepperoni Hot Pockets. What's going on?
-Amily! Amily!

14:35.332 --> 14:38.043
-Oh my God! What are you doing?
-Amily! Amily! Amily!

14:38.127 --> 14:39.795
-Oh my God, all of you.
-No, it's--

14:39.879 --> 14:41.589
What is going on?
You're like feral cats.

14:41.672 --> 14:44.425
No, no, no, no, no.
You tell <i>us </i>what's going on!

14:44.508 --> 14:47.303
We're not privy to the whole picture,
and now you're smelling so good?

14:47.386 --> 14:48.262
-Yeah.
-So good.

